Sorry but if you don't have a good friend who is gay I doubt you would know. People are born gay they don't just decide to be gay over night. Some gay people don't truely know they are gay until later in their life when it just comes out, but previous to that it is truely in the back of their mind.<br>
<br>
I actually used to dislike gay guys because I had the same conception that half of this country has: that gay guys go around having butt sex 24/7 and they only want to get me alone so they can rape me too. Come on I know you guys think this in the back of your minds. But this is far from the truth, it is only a misconception that a few bad individuals started. In fact a lot of gay guys actually keep themselves away from relationships because they are not sure what to do honestly. In fact I met a gay guy and he was one of the nicest people I've met.<br>
<br>
However I will agree that just because someone uses the word gay to describe something doesn't mean they hate gays, but then again it doesn't mean that they don't. I think that someone who doesn't use it is more likely to not be a gay hater though. On the other hand I have another friend that says &quot;I would not be your friend if you turned gay one day&quot; and he doesn't use the word gay because it offends his girlfriend and he doesn't want her to bitch at him. So this can go either way really.<br>
<br>
I see nothing wrong with being gay unless you do something that hurts other people like raping, stalking, or being extremely agressive in flirting with another guy. But this can be wrong for anyone that isn't gay and does it to a woman as well.<br>
<br>
Another thing I think is funny is people who pretend to be elevated when the subject is being talked about openly. Such as my gay friend met my friend that hates gay people, and my gay friend asked the other friend if he didn't like gay people and he said he didn't mind them. What BS that is.<br>
<br>
My advise is basically not to believe what everyone says to you if they know you are gay because of that and there has been a few gay hating incidents like that thing I saw on TV where 4 guys pretended to be gay and took this gay guy from a bar out in the middle of nowhere and killed him just for being gay. Other then that I say more power to gays because you don't see a bunch of gay peopel running around saying they they hate straight people or calling something they dont like &quot;hey your straight person!&quot;.<br>
